{{BLP sources|date=July 2016}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{Hatnote|This is a [[Telugu language|Telugu name]]; the family name is ''Allu''.}} {{Infobox person | name = Allu Sirish | birth_name = Allu Sirish | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1987|5|30}}<ref name="DOB"/> | birth_place = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India | residence = [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]], India | occupation = Actor }} '''Allu Sirish''' ([[Telugu language|Telugu]]:అల్లు శిరీష్) (born 30 May 1987) is an Indian film actor who works predominantly in the [[Telugu film industry]] along with a few [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Malayalam]] films.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Sirish|url=http://www.aggipulla.com/celebrity/allu-sirish-00035747|publisher=Aggipulla}}</ref> Despite acting, Sirish is also the CEO and founder of South-scope magazine. He had also been a co-producer for Ghajini, the Hindi version.
Sirish's debut film was directed by Radha, a Mohasocial l drama ''[[Gouravam (2013 film)|Gouravam]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Sirsh debuts with Gauravam|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-allu-sirish-to-debut-with-gauravam/20121003.htm|publisher=Rediff}}</ref> which was a bi-lingual film shot in Telugu and Tamil, produced by [[Prakash Raj]]. In 1 May 2014, his second film ''Kotha Janta'' was released, starring [[Regina Cassandra]]. His third film is ''[[Srirastu Subhamastu|Srirasthu Subhamastu]]'', which is a family entertainer. This film became the biggest hit in his career. He acted with Mohanlal in a film called ''1971 Beyond Borders'', which was his Malayalam debut. He played a role of soldier for the first time. In 2017, December 28 his film ''[[Okka Kshanam|Okkakshanam]]'' was released, which was directed by [[Vi Anand|VI Anand]] and the casting includes [[Surabhi]], [[Seerat Kapoor]] and [[Srinivas Avasarala]]. The film is a scientific thriller based on the concept of parallel lives.
== Early life == Allu Sirish was born in [[Chennai]] on 30 May 1987. His father [[Allu Aravind]] is a film producer.<ref name="DOB">{{cite web |url=https://www.filmcentro.com/profile/allu-sirish-biography |title=Allu Sirish Biography, Profile, Date of Birth(DOB), Star Sign, Height, Siblings |access-date=2018-11-25 |website=Dosthana |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170917123713/https://www.filmcentro.com/profile/allu-sirish-biography |archive-date=2017-09-17}}</ref> He is the younger brother of actor [[Allu Arjun]] and nephew of [[Chiranjeevi]]. He is the grandson of ''[[Allu Rama Lingaiah]]'', who was an Indian cinema actor who appeared in almost 1000 films.
== Career == Sirish co-produced the film [[Ghajini (2008 film)|''Ghajini'']] along with his father Allu Aravind.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sirsh co-produces Ghajini|url=http://www.bollywoodtrade.com/movies/ghajini/806/|publisher=Bollywood trade}}</ref> Allu Sirish is also a television personality, as he hosts awards shows, such as the ''[[1st IIFA Utsavam|1st]]'' IIFA Utsavam Awards alongside [[Navdeep]] and [[Regina Cassandra]], 64th ''[[Filmfare Awards South]]'' alongside [[Vijay Deverakonda]] and [[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA]] awards alongside [[Lakshmi Manchu]].
