[[Image:Academy-Logo-Color.JPG|thumb|right|CA Academy of Distinguished Neutrals]]

The '''California Academy of Distinguished Neutrals''' is the [[California]]n chapter of the [[National Academy of Distinguished Neutrals]].<ref name="aboutCADN">{{cite web |url=http://www.californianeutrals.org/index.php?rollid=AboutADRWEB |title=About The California Academy of Distinguished Neutrals |author=California Academy of Distinguished Neutrals |authorlink=California Academy of Distinguished Neutrals |publisher=National Academy of Distinguished Neutrals |location=Palm Beach, FL |accessdate=18 July 2012}}</ref>

Membership is limited to [[California]] neutrals who have substantial experience in the resolution of commercial & civil disputes, and who have been recognized for their accomplishments through the Academy's peer-nomination and extensive attorney client review process.<ref name="aboutCADN" />

{{As of|2007|December}}, only 120 such attorneys have been recognized by the group, less than 5% of the state's neutrals.{{Citation needed|date=July 2012}}

